per: Breaking and Making of International Law during the Great War\n  | year         = 2014\n  | publisher    = [[Cornell University Press]]\n  | isbn         = 978-0-8014-5273-4\n  | url          = https://books.google.com/books?id=67xfAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA108&dq=edith+cavell+kaiser&hl=desa=X&ved=0CFcQ6AEwCDgKahUKEwjQ24Owx8HIAhWm_HIKHRzdAaE#v=onepage&q=edith%20cavell%20kaiser&f=false\n  | ref          = harv\n}}\n* {{cite journal\n  | last         = Judson\n  | first        = Helen\n  | date         = Jul 1941\n  | title        = Edith Cavell\n  | journal      = The American Journal of Nursing\n  | publisher    = Lippincott Williams & Wilkins\n  | volume       = 41\n  | issue        = 7\n  | pages        = 871\n  | doi          = 10.2307/3415077\n  | jstor        = 3415077\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Judson|1941}}\n}}\n*{{citation\n |title        = KCACR Roll of Honour\n |url          = http://kcacr.org.uk/county/world-war-1-records/roll-of-honour/\n |publisher    = Kent County Association of Change Ringers\n |accessdate   = 20 December 2016\n |ref          = {{sfnref|KCACR}}\n |url-status      = dead\n |df           = dmy-all\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20161019124918/http://kcacr.org.uk/county/world-war-1-records/roll-of-honour/\n |archive-date = 19 October 2016\n}}\n* {{Cite Americana\n  | last         = Klein\n  | first        = Henri F.\n  | wstitle      = Cavell, Edith\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Encyclopedia Americana|1920}}\n}}\n* {{London Gazette\n  | issue        = 31332\n  |page=5787\n  | date         = 9 May 1919\n}}.\n* {{Cite report\n  | last         = Macdonell\n  | first        = Sir John, KCB (chair)\n  | date         = 26 February 1920\n  | title        = First, Second and Third Interim Reports from the Committee of Enquiry into Breaches of the Laws of War, with Appendices\n  | department   = Cabinet Office: CAB 24/111/13\n  | pages        = 419\u201328\n  | url          = http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/D7736306#imageViewerLink\n  | accessdate   = 17 May 2017\n  | quote        = From These considerations it follows that the Feldgericht was justified in finding that Miss Cavell had committed the offence with which she was charged, and that it had power under the German law with which it was administering to condemn her to death. [p. 424]\n  | ref          = harv\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | last         = Mitchell\n  | first        = David\n  | title        = Cavell Mass\n  | publisher    = Campbell/Bright Morning Star\n  | url          = https://www.sites.google.com/site/brightmorningstar624/home/cavell-mass\n  | accessdate   = 20 June 2015\n  | year         = 2015\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Mitchell|2015}}\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | author        = Monument Australia\n  | year          = 2017\n  | title         = Nurse Edith Cavell\n  | url           = http://monumentaustralia.org.au/themes/people/foreigners/display/32309-nurse-edith-cavell-\n  | accessdate    = 18 May 2017\n  | website       = www.monumentaustralia.org.au\n  | ref           = harv\n}}\n* {{cite news\n  | author       =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->\n  | title        = Seeks Release as Betrayer of Cavell\n  | url          = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KNVeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=QGINAAAAIBAJ&pg=3954,517470&hl=en\n  | newspaper    = The Mount Washington News\n  | date         = 23 February 1934\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|The Mount Washington News|1934}}\n}}\n* {{cite news\n  | last         = Norton-Taylor\n  | first        = Richard\n  | title        = How British diplomats failed Edith Cavell\n  | url          = https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2005/oct/12/freedomofinformation.politics\n  | newspaper    = The Guardian\n  | date         = 12 October 2005\n  | accessdate   = 31 July 2014\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Norton-Taylor|2005}}\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url          = http://www.cathedral.org.uk/historyheritage/historical-characters-linked-in-people-s-minds-eg-dame-julian--sir-thomas-erpingham--edith-cavell