d-New-evidence-that-executed-wartime-nurse-Edith-Cavells-network-was-spying.html\n  | accessdate   = 17 May 2017\n  | ref          = harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n  | last         = Smith\n  | first        = Cindi\n  | title        =  A Parish History of the Church of St. Mary and St. George, Jasper, Alberta\n  | publisher    = Jasper Yellowhead Historical Society\n  | date         = March 1985\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Smith|1985}}\n}}\n* {{cite news\n  | author       =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->\n  | title        = Court Circular\n  | newspaper    = [[The Times]]\n  | location     = London\n  | date         = 14 October 1918\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|The Times|1918}}\n}}\n* {{Cite web\n  | last         = Unger\n  | first        = Abraham\n  | title        = Edith Cavell\n  | work         = HistoryNet\n  | accessdate   = 1 December 2015\n  | date         = 23 September 1997\n  | url          =http://www.britishheritage.com/edith-cavell/\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Unger|1997}}\n}}\n* {{Cite web\n  | last         = Watson\n  | first        = Greig\n  | title        = World War One: Edith Cavell and Charles Fryatt 'martyred'\n  | work         = BBC News\n  | accessdate   = 31 July 2014\n  | date         = 24 February 2014\n  | url          = https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-25244361\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Watson|2014|}}\n}}\n* {{Cite web\n  | last         = Walker\n  | first        = Alan\n  | title        = Walter Percival Starmer: Artist 1877\u20131961\n  \n  | date         = April 2015a\n  | url          = http://www.walterpstarmer.com\n  | accessdate   = 24 November 2017\n  | ref          = {{sfnref|Walker|2015a}}\n}}\n* {{Cite web\n  | last         = Walker\n  | first        = Alan\n  | title        = Campaign from on high at St Jude's\n  | date         = 31 July 2015b\n  \n  | url          = https://www.churchtimes.co.uk/articles/2015/31-july/features/features/campaign-from-on-high-at-st-jude-s\n  | accessdate   = 24 November 2017\n  | websit